# Form Module Guide

The form module handles form creation, rendering, and submission. Key components and files:

## Components
- [src/modules/form/components/front/detail/form.tsx](mdc:src/modules/form/components/front/detail/form.tsx) - Main form component
- [src/modules/form/components/front/detail/form-item.tsx](mdc:src/modules/form/components/front/detail/form-item.tsx) - Individual form field component

## Types
- [src/modules/form/types/form.ts](mdc:src/modules/form/types/form.ts) - Form-related TypeScript types

## Services
- [src/modules/form/services/form-service.ts](mdc:src/modules/form/services/form-service.ts) - Form-related API services

## Form Features
- Form validation using plugin schemas
- Internationalization support
- Dynamic field rendering
- Form submission handling
- Field numbering styles
- Required field indicators

## Usage
Forms are rendered using the `Form` component which accepts:
- `form`: Form configuration object
- `schemas`: Array of plugin schemas for validation
